criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Persistent pain: NRS score >2 in at least 5 assessments in 5 consecutive days, despite
             usual antalgic management;

          -  Spinal cord injury due to any etiology (both traumatic and non-traumatic);

          -  Spinal cord injury of any neurological level, complete or incomplete, classifiable as
             Asia Impairment Score (AIS) A, B, C or D;

          -  Stable medical conditions;

          -  At least 1 month away from the spinal cord injury event.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Sporadic pain;

          -  Mechanical ventilation;

          -  Pregnancy;

          -  Disorders of consciousness;

          -  Incapacity to give informed consent in person.
